Our Story

A Baker Born
from Passion

Since 2019, this kitchen has been a place of discovery, discipline, and deep love for the craft. Formally trained in Culinary Arts, the chef behind Naomi's Pies has spent years perfecting her art — not following recipes, but creating them.

From her signature blueberry-ginger pie to rich savory quiches made with farm-fresh custard, every bite tells a story of someone who chose quality over convenience — every single time.

Now rooted in Leander and eager to share her craft with the greater Austin community, she invites you to taste the difference that real ingredients, real training, and real love make.

How to Order

Ways to Enjoy
Naomi's Pies

01

Pickup Orders

Order ahead and pick up your custom pies fresh from the oven. Available in Leander. Perfect for gift-giving, dinner parties, or simply treating yourself to something extraordinary.

02

Catering

Hosting a gathering, brunch, corporate event, or celebration? We love feeding groups. Mini pies, hand pies, and quiche platters make any event unforgettable. Let's talk about your vision.

03

Pop-Up Events

We're actively seeking partnerships with Austin-area markets, women's groups, and community events. If you run a local market or organization and want to share something special, we'd love to connect.

The Crust Promise

Handmade Amish Crust,
Every Time

No shortcuts. No frozen dough. Every crust is made by hand using shortening — making it completely vegan, perfectly flaky, and deeply flavorful. It's the foundation everything is built on, and it shows in every single bite.

  • Shortening-based crust — naturally vegan
  • No preservatives or artificial ingredients
  • Shortening crust — vegan & dairy-free
  • No canned fruit — ever
  • Original, invented recipes
  • Culinary Arts trained since 2019

Our Community

Rooted in Leander,
Reaching Austin

Naomi's Pies was built for women who love homemade things, for homemakers who want to be inspired, and for anyone who believes that the best food comes from someone who truly cares. We're looking to grow with our community — through local markets, pop-up events, and partnerships with groups that share our values.
